author: tomj
msg: Rearrange the doGet() function a bit and add some comments.
Check to see if we are doing a list or WSDL request before trying to
present the user with a list of services and remove the check for the
hardcoded JWS extension.  In particular, if a handler is registered
for some other file extension, this check may prevent them from doing their
thing.
Made getHttpServletResponseStatus protected as requested
by Frederick N. Brier [mailto:fbrier@multideck.com]

author: tomj
msg: Relax protection level on a few variables and functions as requested by
Frederick N. Brier [fbrier@multideck.com].

author: tomj
msg: Fix a bug handling parameters of type double or long, which occupy two
slots in the local variable table.
Update Built in bytecode reader to be the default.
This removes Axis dependancy on tt-bytecode.jar (or any other bytecode jar).
We can now remove the Extractor factory and support for other bytecode readers
if we want, and use this class as the single way to check for debug info in
class files.
We will let this code soak a bit before we do anything too drastic however.

author: gdaniels
msg: Remove buggy code (we shouldn't be producing any schema at all for
xsd/soap-enc types - that's the job of those schemas!).
